summaries.short: Thackery attempts to make a conditional return to The Knick as Edwards struggles between ambition and reality.
summaries.full: Thackery sets his sights on a return to The Knick--a request that doesn't sit well with the Board. After a shocking discovery, Cornelia enlists Cleary to do a dirty job, for a price. Bertie makes a change; Henry Robertson pushes a new subway initiative; Barrow drives up construction costs; Lucy is surprised by an unexpected visitor from home.

summaries.short: Michael Begler, Jack Amiel and Michael Angarano dissect an eyeball and explore The Knick's world of props.
summaries.full: Michael Begler, Jack Amiel and Michael Angarano dissect an eyeball and explore The Knick's world of props.

titles.short: The Best with the Best to Get the Best
titles.full: The Best with the Best to Get the Best

summaries.short: Thackery enlists Edwards to help with an ambitious experiment; Lucy makes a confession.
summaries.full: Thackery enlists Edwards to help him test a new hypothesis. After rejecting Henry Robertson's advances at The Knick, Lucy learns that confession isn't always good for the soul. We meet Genevieve Everidge, a young journalist writing a story about a rival doctor. Cornelia is dismayed by the limits of Philip's sympathies; Barrow faces a new adversary at Tammany Hall.

summaries.short: Season 2 Premiere. Thackery struggles to kick his habit while The Knick prepares its move uptown.
summaries.full: Season 2 Premiere. As Barrow and The Knick prepare to move uptown, Edwards lobbies the hospital board to be appointed permanent head of surgery. Though his suspension has been lifted, Gallinger refuses to return as Edwards' subordinate, so he heads to Cromartie Hospital in hopes of getting Thackery to return to work. Lucy's attempts to make amends with Bertie are rebuffed.

summaries.short: Cast members Eve Hewson and Chris Sullivan talk accents, character development and the camaraderie of the cast and crew.
summaries.full: Cast members Eve Hewson and Chris Sullivan talk accents, character development and the camaraderie of the cast and crew.

summaries.short: Thackery puts his syphilis treatment to the ultimate test; Harriet's day in court arrives.
summaries.full: Abby's worsening condition persuades Thackery to test out his novel syphilis treatment. Algernon comes clean to Opal, but does not get the response he expects. Cleary makes a last-ditch effort to raise funds for Harriet as her date in court arrives. Bertie undergoes physical training; Barrow loses a sponsor; Gallinger's prejudices are reinforced.

summaries.short: The Knick's Dr. Bertram Chickering Jr, played by Michael Angarano, helps recap season one before diving into the Season 2 premiere.
summaries.full: The Knick's Dr. Bertram Chickering Jr, played by Michael Angarano, helps recap season one before diving into the Season 2 premiere.

summaries.short: Season finale. Thackery pushes himself to the limit and beyond; Cornelia and Edwards arrive at a crossroads.
summaries.full: Season finale. Refusing to collaborate with Dr. Zinberg on blood-transfusion research, an increasingly paranoid Thackery pushes himself to the limit, and beyond, in an effort to solve the riddle and beat his rival. Cornelia and Edwards arrive at a crossroads; Barrow trades one creditor for another; Lucy requests Bertie's help.

summaries.short: Chris Sullivan joins show writers Michael Begler and Jack Amiel to discuss explosions, syphilis noses and removing modernity from Brooklyn.
summaries.full: Chris Sullivan joins show writers Michael Begler and Jack Amiel to discuss explosions, syphilis noses and removing modernity from Brooklyn.

summaries.short: A subway explosion leads to pandemonium at The Knick; Thackery finds a test case for his addiction theory.
summaries.full: A subway explosion leads to an influx of patients at The Knick, but little margin for profit. Pursued by Henry, Lucy takes to heart some advice given by one of Ping Wu's girls. An addict's misfortune gives Thackery an ideal test case for his latest theory on addiction. Bertie submits his adrenalin research to Zinberg; Cornelia gets a new clue in Speight's death.

summaries.short: Lucy goes to extremes to get drugs for Thackery; Cornelia and Edwards face a dilemma.
summaries.full: A late-night crime sheds unfavorable light on The Knick, forcing Robertson to come up with hush money. Lucy goes to extremes to get drugs for a desperate Thackery, whose plea for an advance from a seller of patent medicines falls on deaf ears. Gallinger despairs as Eleanor's behavior becomes more erratic; Cornelia and Edwards proffer different solutions to a shared dilemma.

summaries.short: Jack and Michael talk with location manager Rob Striem about the where, the how and the food behind filming on location.
summaries.full: Jack and Michael talk with location manager Rob Striem about the where, the how and the food behind filming on location.
